WEBVTT

00:03.586 --> 00:06.588
And now, please welcome
your valedictorian, Alex Dunphy.

00:09.343 --> 00:11.051
##  

00:15.432 --> 00:17.923
Where are my mom and dad?

00:20.771 --> 00:23.440
And in this corner,
finishing first in her class...

00:23.524 --> 00:26.690
delivering the commencement address,
weighing in at...

00:26.777 --> 00:28.437
- What do you weigh, honey?
- Dad!

00:28.529 --> 00:31.613
A healthy amount for a girl her age...

00:31.698 --> 00:33.572
- Are you gettin' all this, buddy?
- Pure gold.

00:33.659 --> 00:36.031
She's the main brain,
the cerebellum of the ball...

00:36.119 --> 00:38.990
Alex Dunphy!

00:39.081 --> 00:42.165
Oh, keep rolling. The news will want this
footage when I eventually snap.

00:42.251 --> 00:44.124
I thought Sanjay Patel
was first in the class.

00:44.211 --> 00:45.670
He was until he missed a few weeks...

00:45.754 --> 00:47.296
and the robot
he was building attacked him.

00:47.381 --> 00:50.501
It's happening, people.
Our hubris will be our undoing.

00:50.592 --> 00:53.344
Sweetie, what do you say
you and I go and get our nails done, huh?

00:53.428 --> 00:56.098
- It's okay. I wanna work on my speech.
 Been there.

00:56.181 --> 01:00.179
I remember the speech that won me
treasurer of my high school Spanish club.

01:00.269 --> 01:03.388
<i>Mi nombre es Felipe.</i>

01:03.480 --> 01:05.473
<i>Yo voy a la escuela...</i>

01:05.566 --> 01:07.024
Felipe?

01:07.109 --> 01:08.603
It was kind of a <i>grande</i> deal.

01:08.694 --> 01:10.603
I was up against an actual Puerto Rican.

01:10.696 --> 01:12.523
Honey, are you sure?

01:12.614 --> 01:14.441
Because I think
they can do school colors.

01:14.533 --> 01:16.241
- I'm good, Mom.
- Okay.

01:16.326 --> 01:20.276
<i>  Family milestones</i>
<i>always throw Claire for a loop.</i>

01:20.372 --> 01:22.163
She holds it in, and then the next day...

01:22.249 --> 01:25.285
she has a total meltdown
and I have to pick up the pieces.

01:25.377 --> 01:27.037
The problem is...

01:27.129 --> 01:29.371
tomorrow I'm supposed to go
to Vegas with my buds...

01:29.464 --> 01:33.083
so I need her to melt down today.

01:33.177 --> 01:37.257
Otherwise, what happens in Vegas won't
happen to me, because I won't be there.

01:37.347 --> 01:39.091
Emotional day, huh?

01:39.183 --> 01:41.341
Happy day.

01:41.435 --> 01:44.186
- Happy and sad.
- Hmm.

01:46.064 --> 01:47.607
<i>"Guys, I can't go to Vegas...</i>

01:47.691 --> 01:49.767
because my wife's freaking out."

01:49.860 --> 01:51.899
Trust me, that is not
a phone call you wanna make...

01:51.987 --> 01:54.822
to a bunch of ex-college
male cheerleaders.

01:54.907 --> 01:58.110
They will mock you
with a hurtful rhythmic taunt.

02:03.999 --> 02:04.995
Hello?

02:05.083 --> 02:07.206
- Gloria, it's me.
- Hi. How was the doctor?

02:07.294 --> 02:09.583
Can you pick up some bread
on the way home, please?

02:09.670 --> 02:12.625
I'm home. My damn gate remote
won't work. Could you press...

02:12.716 --> 02:14.210
- <i>  Hello?</i>
...nine?

02:14.301 --> 02:16.009
- Manny, it's okay.
- <i>What's okay?</i>

02:16.094 --> 02:19.510
- What's wrong? Where are you calling from?
- <i>I'm not calling from.</i>

02:19.598 --> 02:21.923
- Jay is calling.
- What's wrong with Jay?

02:22.017 --> 02:24.175
- My clicker won't work.
- <i>Oh, my God.</i>

02:24.269 --> 02:27.021
Your heart's not working? How could
you tell us this over the phone?

02:27.105 --> 02:28.600
<i>My heart is fine.</i>

02:28.690 --> 02:31.442
Would somebody please press nine
and let me in?

02:31.527 --> 02:33.649
- Okay.
- Got it.

02:33.737 --> 02:35.895
It won't work
if you're both on the line.

02:35.989 --> 02:37.234
- Okay.
- <i>Okay.</i>

02:39.117 --> 02:41.691
Every damn time!

02:44.289 --> 02:46.448
Okay, Lily, time to get dressed.

02:46.542 --> 02:48.914
I can't believe Alex
is gonna be in high school.

02:49.002 --> 02:51.042
- I feel so old.
- You feel old?

02:51.129 --> 02:54.296
I was there when she was born...
in the delivery room.

02:54.383 --> 02:56.375
- If I wasn't gay before...
- Oh, please.

02:56.468 --> 02:58.128
You wouldn't have lasted
two minutes on a farm.

02:58.220 --> 03:00.426
I've witnessed all kinds of birthing.
Never batted an eye.

03:00.514 --> 03:02.803
I've seen cattle.
I've seen hogs. I've seen goats.

03:02.891 --> 03:04.931
I've even seen the three-legged...
Oh! Whoa!

03:05.018 --> 03:07.556
Oh, my God.

03:07.646 --> 03:10.433
Oh, my God.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.433
- I'm sorry.
- Really, Mitchell?

03:12.526 --> 03:13.901
I could have just died.

03:19.575 --> 03:21.401
<i># Hey, hey #</i>

03:21.493 --> 03:23.616
<i># Hey, hey #</i>

03:23.704 --> 03:25.743
<i># Hey, hey #</i>

03:25.831 --> 03:27.622
<i># Hey, hey #</i>

03:27.708 --> 03:29.036
<i># Hey ##.</i>

03:31.753 --> 03:34.957
Principal Kaizler, faculty,
parents, fellow graduates...

03:35.048 --> 03:36.958
Hey, superstar.

03:37.050 --> 03:39.339
- Oh, you're working on your speech.
- Yep.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.005
Do you need any help?

03:41.096 --> 03:44.014
Sometimes it's great to bounce ideas
off someone whose opinion you value.

03:44.099 --> 03:45.843
- I'm good.
- Okay.

03:45.934 --> 03:48.769
That's cool I could do your hair.

03:48.854 --> 03:51.012
We could do it like we saw
in that magazine on...

03:51.106 --> 03:53.063
What's that actress?
What's her name? With the teeth?

03:53.150 --> 03:55.356
Mom, Mom, please.
I'm trying to concentrate.

03:55.444 --> 03:57.816
Okay. Okay.

03:57.905 --> 03:59.862
You be ready to go in a half hour...

03:59.948 --> 04:01.692
'cause we are gonna carpool
with your grandpa.

04:01.783 --> 04:04.453
Haley's driving me.
I wanna get there early.

04:05.454 --> 04:06.996
That's a great idea.

04:07.080 --> 04:08.872
Great. I will see you there...

04:08.957 --> 04:10.451
superstar.

04:12.002 --> 04:15.916
- Hey, Mama Bear. You okay?
- Not with "Mama Bear" I'm not.

04:16.005 --> 04:17.548
- Don't cry.
- I'm not crying.

04:17.632 --> 04:19.459
Shh! Don't be brave.

04:19.551 --> 04:21.459
I'm here for you...

04:21.553 --> 04:25.503
...until 2:00 p.m. tomorrow,
when my flight leaves for Vegas.

04:26.934 --> 04:28.973
Where were you?
Did you bring the bread?

04:29.061 --> 04:31.896
I was stuck outside that gate
for 10 minutes before it opened.

04:31.980 --> 04:34.388
- So no bread?
- We gotta get that thing fixed.

04:34.483 --> 04:36.974
- <i>Ay,</i> what happened to your eye?
- What are you talking about?

04:37.069 --> 04:39.108
- It's droopy.
- What do you mean, droopy?

04:39.196 --> 04:42.612
Uh! I don't like the look of that, Jay.
Here. Let me check something.

04:42.699 --> 04:44.775
Put that thing away.
I saw my dermatologist.

04:44.868 --> 04:46.528
He was checking for moles or something.

04:46.620 --> 04:48.659
He probably got some
numbing cream on it. It's fine.

04:49.706 --> 04:51.201
Nothin' to worry about.

04:52.376 --> 04:54.452
I got Botox.

04:54.545 --> 04:58.127
Stupid doctor talked me into it,
and now it's drifting.

04:58.215 --> 05:00.788
I haven't felt this dumb
since I shelled out 30 bucks...

05:00.884 --> 05:03.755
for that bracelet,
supposed to give me better balance.

05:03.846 --> 05:05.589
- Try to push my arm down.
- Okay.

05:05.681 --> 05:07.424
- Go ahead. You can't do it.
- Okay. All right.

05:07.516 --> 05:10.517
Honey, I'm home!
Hey, why is your dad's car here?

05:14.815 --> 05:17.520
It's ironic that I stand up here
representing my classmates...

05:17.609 --> 05:19.353
when, for the past three years...

05:19.444 --> 05:21.935
most of them have treated me
like I'm invisible.

05:22.030 --> 05:25.565
It's my own fault. I was obsessed
with good grades instead of looks...

05:25.659 --> 05:27.616
popularity and skinny jeans.

05:27.703 --> 05:29.612
- What? Is that your speech?
- Get out of here!

05:29.705 --> 05:31.496
You cannot say that!

05:31.582 --> 05:34.369
Yes, I can. And you wanna know why?
'Cause it's the truth.

05:34.459 --> 05:37.626
No one wants to hear the truth.
It's very simple, Alex.

05:37.713 --> 05:41.129
In order to give a good speech, all you
have to do is take a song and say it...

05:41.216 --> 05:44.632
like "Don't Stop Believing,"
or "Get this Party Started."

05:44.720 --> 05:46.178
That's means nothing.

05:46.263 --> 05:48.884
Who cares? Nobody wants to think.

05:48.974 --> 05:52.010
It's a graduation...
a celebration of being done with thinking.

05:52.102 --> 05:53.810
People want to be challenged.

05:53.896 --> 05:55.639
They're gonna respect me for it.

05:55.731 --> 05:58.186
No one's ever gonna talk to you again.

05:58.275 --> 05:59.817
So what?

05:59.902 --> 06:03.152
Mahatma Gandhi went on a hunger strike
for what he believed in.

06:03.238 --> 06:06.856
That's 'cause no one
would eat with him in the cafeteria.

06:08.368 --> 06:09.863
Hmm.

06:14.374 --> 06:16.414
- Hey.
 Hey, guys.

06:16.502 --> 06:18.328
Come on over.
Have some lemonade and cookies.

06:18.420 --> 06:20.496
- Jay, that's not looking very good.
- It's fine.

06:20.589 --> 06:21.964
Quick. Who's the president.

06:22.049 --> 06:24.172
- Obama!
- Phil, please.

06:24.259 --> 06:26.501
- I'm trying to rule out a stroke.
- It's not a stroke.

06:26.595 --> 06:28.967
Why does everybody always assume
I'm having a stroke?

06:29.056 --> 06:30.218
 Age.
- Diet.

06:30.307 --> 06:32.098
You forgot to bring my bread.

06:32.184 --> 06:33.512
- I'm sorry we're late.
 It's okay.

06:33.602 --> 06:35.476
We gotta leave
in about five minutes though.

06:35.562 --> 06:38.433
Luke, stop pushing that ball around.
You're gonna fall in.

06:38.524 --> 06:40.931
Oh, yes, and then your Uncle Mitchell
will laugh at your expense.

06:41.026 --> 06:43.647
- I'm just saying. It's a character flaw.

06:43.737 --> 06:45.196
Okay, quick poll here.

06:45.280 --> 06:47.736
This morning, Cam... fully dressed...

06:47.824 --> 06:49.367
Thank God it's one of those stories.

06:49.451 --> 06:52.025
 ... while in the middle
of a very serious thought...

06:52.120 --> 06:53.912
fell into a ducky pool.

06:53.997 --> 06:56.453
Oh, my goodness. Are you all right?

06:56.542 --> 07:00.539
Yes, I am. Thank you. That is
a normal reaction... Love and concern.

07:00.629 --> 07:02.123
Okay, wait, wait.

07:02.214 --> 07:04.586
The pool popped.

07:05.634 --> 07:07.342
<i>Ay,</i> poor thing.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.753
- There's nothing worse than a tailbone injury.
- Seriously?

07:09.847 --> 07:12.219
No, no, no. You're so full of it.
You know this is funny.

07:12.307 --> 07:14.715
Picture this...

07:14.810 --> 07:17.217
falling into a tiny pool.

07:18.480 --> 07:20.272
He'll be here all week, folks...

07:20.357 --> 07:21.982
literally, because
you're not coming home with me.

07:22.067 --> 07:24.475
- There she is. There's my little Stella.

07:24.570 --> 07:26.443
That's my girl. Hi, sweetie.

07:26.530 --> 07:28.439
You're so cute
I just want to eat your face!

07:28.532 --> 07:30.026
- Aww.
- Mmm.

07:30.117 --> 07:32.406
You remember when
you used to hold Alex like that...

07:32.494 --> 07:34.368
- and you wanted to eat her face?
- Yeah.

07:34.454 --> 07:36.246
- Now she's off to high school.
- Mmm.

07:36.331 --> 07:38.371
- Time marches on, huh?
- Yep.

07:38.458 --> 07:40.202
- You know what's really sad?
- What?

07:40.294 --> 07:42.500
The end of <i>Titanic.</i>

07:42.588 --> 07:44.082
Hey, Luke.

07:44.173 --> 07:47.339
Do you realize in two years
you and I will be graduating?

07:47.426 --> 07:48.920
Not now.

07:49.011 --> 07:51.299
I think I'm moving the ball with my mind.

07:51.388 --> 07:53.594
Well, I'll be graduating.

07:54.933 --> 07:56.842
Hey, you know, you guys,
stop congratulating yourselves...

07:56.935 --> 07:58.762
for being <i>so</i> compassionate.

07:58.854 --> 08:01.475
If you had been there, you would have
laughed just as hard as I did.

08:01.565 --> 08:04.352
He's coming. Stop talking.
He's been embarrassed enough today.

08:08.155 --> 08:11.606
 Stop.

08:14.912 --> 08:16.951
Wow. Now it makes sense.

08:17.039 --> 08:18.699
It's a Pritchett thing.

08:20.000 --> 08:22.871
Cruelty's genetic.
Suddenly it's all very clear.

08:22.961 --> 08:25.452
Be careful. You might run into it.

08:27.007 --> 08:29.759
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry, Cam. I'm sorry.

08:29.843 --> 08:31.800
- Oh, my God. Dad, your face.
- What?

08:31.887 --> 08:33.760
Oh, that's nothing. Nothing. It's boring.

08:33.847 --> 08:35.639
I went to the dermatologist.
It's a boring story.

08:35.724 --> 08:37.681
No, no, no.
We gotta get you to a hospital.

08:37.768 --> 08:39.595
- I'm fine.
- Yes. I'm taking you. Come.

08:39.686 --> 08:41.644
- <i>¡ Vamos!</i>
- Wait. Wait right here.

08:41.730 --> 08:43.639
Gloria. Gloria!

08:45.734 --> 08:47.109
Gloria.

08:47.194 --> 08:48.605
Gloria. Gloria, hold on.

08:48.695 --> 08:51.365
The reason my face looks like this
is because I had...

08:51.448 --> 08:53.108
Botox.

08:54.201 --> 08:56.407
Like the ladies use for their wrinkles?

08:56.495 --> 08:59.033
Actually, nearly 10% of their sales
are men, but that's not important.

08:59.122 --> 09:01.660
I had a bad reaction...
Hit a nerve or something.

09:01.750 --> 09:03.375
It's gonna go away soon.

09:03.460 --> 09:06.081
- Hmm.
- What? What's that supposed to mean?

09:07.256 --> 09:08.750
- Nothing.
- Would you stop?

09:08.841 --> 09:11.166
This is very embarrassing for me.

09:12.261 --> 09:13.921
For both of us.

09:17.933 --> 09:20.768
He's fine. It was a false alarm.

09:20.853 --> 09:22.975
What do you mean, a false alarm?
His face looks like a candle.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.723
You heard her. I'm okay.

09:24.815 --> 09:27.021
- She's not a doctor.
- Neither are you.

09:27.109 --> 09:28.568
- Technically.
- Okay, look.

09:28.652 --> 09:30.775
I don't know what's going on here,
but there is no way...

09:30.863 --> 09:32.440
that <i>this</i> is normal.

09:32.531 --> 09:35.401
You look like a Botox job
gone horribly wrong.

09:35.492 --> 09:38.529
No, my God... You didn't.

09:38.620 --> 09:41.158
Of course he didn't.
  Did you?

09:42.916 --> 09:44.494
- No.

09:44.585 --> 09:47.455
- You did!
- What were you thinking? You're a veteran.

09:47.546 --> 09:49.420
Enough! This conversation is ended.

09:49.506 --> 09:51.831
Let's go.

09:51.925 --> 09:54.962
Do you think he got his butt done too?
It looks fantastic.

09:57.139 --> 09:59.760
Alex, wait. I'm sorry.

09:59.850 --> 10:01.926
If you wanna give your speech, go ahead.

10:02.019 --> 10:03.846
I was never valedictorian.
What do I know?

10:03.937 --> 10:05.218
Thank you!

10:05.314 --> 10:06.974
I am doing this for a reason.

10:07.065 --> 10:08.608
- It's not just like I'm...
- Aha!

10:08.692 --> 10:11.978
Sorry, Alex,
but you will thank me one day.

10:12.070 --> 10:15.689
Please. You really think
I don't have duplicates?

10:15.782 --> 10:17.905
If you do this you'll be a social piranha.

10:17.993 --> 10:21.991
Yes. I'll be an Amazonian
carnivorous fish.

10:22.789 --> 10:24.912
Carniv... What?

