- Dad, open the gate.
- Aw, geez. Not now!

10:36.220 --> 10:37.595
What? What's happening?

10:37.679 --> 10:39.257
It's stuck again.

10:39.348 --> 10:41.506
What do you mean it's stuck?
Can't you get it open?

10:41.600 --> 10:43.391
What do you think "stuck" means, Claire?

10:43.477 --> 10:46.976
We have to do something, Dad.
Can't you push it open or something?

10:47.064 --> 10:50.349
- I don't know.
- We are trapped in your driveway...

10:50.442 --> 10:52.102
and you don't know?

10:52.194 --> 10:54.815
As a gate owner, Dad,
you have a certain responsibility.

10:54.905 --> 10:59.033
See, my daughter is gonna get up
on that stage and give a speech...

10:59.117 --> 11:01.953
and graduate from middle school, and
if I am not there I am going to freak out.

11:02.037 --> 11:03.745
- I am going to freak out!
 Let me push it.

11:03.830 --> 11:05.953
Do you have any idea how important it is...

11:06.041 --> 11:08.330
- Why are you smiling?
- I'm not. I'm not smiling.

11:08.418 --> 11:10.292
Do you not understand me?

11:10.379 --> 11:15.586
Chu-chunk. Hysterical wife,
hysterical wife, hysterical wife...

11:16.677 --> 11:18.171
Jackpot.

11:22.641 --> 11:24.799
- Oh, God. Come on!

11:24.893 --> 11:26.518
All right. Okay. We have tried this way.

11:26.603 --> 11:28.643
I say we ram the gate.
Kids, get out of the way.

11:28.730 --> 11:30.806
Hold on. I think I can fix this.

11:30.899 --> 11:34.849
- I just need a paper clip, some olive oil and a ribbon.
- What's the plan, "MacGayver"?

11:34.945 --> 11:37.697
Actually, the paper clip
is to connect these two circuits...

11:37.781 --> 11:39.774
and the olive oil is
to lubricate the mechanism.

11:39.867 --> 11:42.737
And the hair ribbon is for Lily.
Her hair's been driving me crazy all day.

11:42.828 --> 11:44.488
Why don't we just call some cabs?

11:44.580 --> 11:47.035
Because, Mitchell, this is not
Times Square and they'll take forever.

11:47.124 --> 11:49.662
- We'll just climb over the fence and start running.
- No, we won't...

11:49.751 --> 11:52.159
because it's five miles away, Phil,
and I'm in big shoes.

11:52.254 --> 11:53.748
So no.

11:53.839 --> 11:56.709
Wait, wait, wait! I save the day.

11:56.800 --> 11:59.125
Let's take this crazy bicycle.

11:59.219 --> 12:00.761
We throw it over the gate...

12:00.846 --> 12:02.673
then we take Phil and we take Claire...

12:02.764 --> 12:05.255
and then we throw them over the gate too.

12:05.350 --> 12:07.343
- What the hell is that?
- Jay bought it.

12:07.436 --> 12:09.263
He thought we were gonna
use it all the time...

12:09.354 --> 12:12.272
- but I keep hitting my boobs with my knees.
- Champagne problems, right?

12:12.357 --> 12:14.397
Honey, they're not gonna ride the bike.

12:14.484 --> 12:17.189
Yeah, but I still think
that we should throw it over the gate.

12:17.279 --> 12:18.903
Okay. You know what?
Thank you. Thank you.

12:18.989 --> 12:20.946
Nobody else has come up with an idea.

12:21.033 --> 12:22.776
I think I've got a good idea.

12:22.868 --> 12:24.991
We don't have time
to build a rocket, buddy.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.786
Never mind.

12:26.872 --> 12:29.873
Okay. So Phil and I will go over first...

12:29.958 --> 12:32.628
- and then you guys will throw over the bike.
- Step up. I'll boost you.

12:32.711 --> 12:34.336
- Couldn't we get a ladder?
- Please.

12:34.421 --> 12:37.292
On cheer squad I boosted girls bigger
than you to the top of a human pyramid.

12:37.382 --> 12:38.925
Now, arms at your side.

12:39.009 --> 12:40.966
Straight like a pencil.

12:41.053 --> 12:42.547
One, two...

12:42.638 --> 12:45.211
- # We are Bulldogs #
- Aaah!

12:45.307 --> 12:46.801
Ow!

12:47.643 --> 12:49.434
She's fine. Okay.

12:49.520 --> 12:51.311
Jay, now you do me.

12:53.440 --> 12:55.231
Just grab a handful. Don't be shy.

12:55.317 --> 12:56.977
I'm not giving you as much to work with.

12:57.069 --> 12:58.896
I used to have a lot more there.
I lost it.

12:58.987 --> 13:00.897
They used to call me the Grand Can.

13:06.787 --> 13:08.779
It's ironic that I stand up here...

13:08.872 --> 13:11.410
representing my classmates
when, for the past...

13:11.500 --> 13:14.038
- I read the rest of your speech.
- Congratulations.

13:15.170 --> 13:17.412
- Do you hate me?
- What?

13:17.506 --> 13:20.044
You talk about how all the popular kids
are shallow and lame.

13:20.133 --> 13:22.838
- I didn't mean you.
- You think you have everyone figured out...

13:22.928 --> 13:24.885
but everybody has their stuff.

13:24.972 --> 13:26.845
What <i>stuff</i> do you have?

13:26.932 --> 13:29.803
Too many boys chasing after you?
Too many parties?

13:29.893 --> 13:33.309
- You really wanna know what stuff I have?
- Yeah.

13:33.397 --> 13:36.932
I'm flunking out of Biology,
and now I have to go to summer school.

13:37.025 --> 13:40.774
My friends, all they can ever talk about
nowadays is going off to college...

13:40.863 --> 13:42.985
and I don't even know
if I can get into college.

13:43.073 --> 13:44.733
Is that enough stuff for you?

13:44.825 --> 13:47.363
- Whatever.
- You know what?

13:47.452 --> 13:50.157
Fine. Give your stupid speech.
Be an outcast.

13:50.247 --> 13:53.367
But you're only doing it to yourself,
because you're smart and pretty...

13:53.458 --> 13:55.617
and sort of funny
in a way that I don't really get...

13:55.711 --> 13:57.371
but other people seem to enjoy.

13:57.462 --> 13:59.538
So you can either start fresh next year...

13:59.631 --> 14:02.502
or be the freak who flipped off her class.

14:02.593 --> 14:03.873
You really think I'm pretty?

14:03.969 --> 14:05.511
Shut up!

14:11.226 --> 14:12.886
- Phil, go straight!
- This way's faster.

14:12.978 --> 14:14.472
- No, straight.
- Stop leaning!

14:14.563 --> 14:16.022
- Do you wanna drive?
- I do.

14:16.106 --> 14:18.265
Tough. I called it.

14:18.358 --> 14:19.473
- What was that?

14:19.568 --> 14:21.607
Oh, crap. The chain broke.

14:21.695 --> 14:23.189
Just keep pedaling. It doesn't matter.

14:23.280 --> 14:25.071
It matters a little.

14:25.157 --> 14:27.149
Cam, please be careful.

14:27.242 --> 14:29.199
Why? If I get electrocuted
my hat might blow off...

14:29.286 --> 14:30.994
and that would be funny as hell, right?

14:31.079 --> 14:32.787
No. No.

14:34.208 --> 14:36.165
Hey, Jay!

14:36.251 --> 14:37.793
I know you're feeling self-conscious...

14:37.878 --> 14:41.163
- so I dug up something I thought might help.
- Put that thing away.

14:41.256 --> 14:43.213
I knew you'd say that, but hear me out.

14:43.300 --> 14:46.835
This was designed to make a
hideously disfigured man look super cool.

14:46.929 --> 14:49.336
It's perfect for you. Ooh, yikes.

14:49.431 --> 14:52.432
Okay, I'll go upstairs
and see if I have a lefty.

14:55.771 --> 14:57.645
Don't look at me like that.

14:57.731 --> 15:01.776
I have to say that I am a little
disappointed in you doing this thing.

15:01.860 --> 15:04.019
Not me. I feel real good about it.

15:04.112 --> 15:05.737
How many times do I have to tell you...

15:05.822 --> 15:08.693
- that you don't have to look young for me?
- I didn't do it for you.

15:08.784 --> 15:10.823
- What is her name?
- Stop.

15:10.911 --> 15:14.576
Most of the time I walk around,
in my head, I'm 40.

15:14.665 --> 15:16.289
And I look in the mirror...

15:16.375 --> 15:19.292
I say, "Who's that old man?
What's he doing in my bathroom?"

15:19.378 --> 15:23.506
Well, it's my bathroom too,
and I like when the old guy is there.

15:23.590 --> 15:27.125
This is the face that I fell in love with.

15:27.219 --> 15:28.927
Not this face...

15:29.012 --> 15:30.637
- this one.
 Oh. Ooh!

15:30.722 --> 15:32.549
- The gate's opening. The gate's opening!
- How did you do that?

15:32.641 --> 15:34.301
- I didn't do anything.
- I did it.

15:34.393 --> 15:36.551
I opened it with my mind.

15:36.645 --> 15:38.056
Come on, guys.
Let's go, guys. Saddle up!

15:38.146 --> 15:39.605
- <i>¡ Vamos!</i>
 I'll get the car seat.

15:39.690 --> 15:42.477
Get Manny. Get Manny.
Everyone in the car. Let's go!

15:42.609 --> 15:42.651
Yep, that's what I thought.

15:42.651 --> 15:44.394
Yep, that's what I thought.

15:44.486 --> 15:46.194
Chain's broken.

15:46.280 --> 15:48.319
What do you think?

15:48.407 --> 15:50.649
I think we gotta go.

15:50.742 --> 15:53.743
Sweetie, we can't make it on foot.

15:53.829 --> 15:55.240
We have to try.

15:56.290 --> 15:57.867
Honey.

15:57.958 --> 15:59.832
Honey! It's okay.

15:59.918 --> 16:02.290
It's not okay, Phil. It's not okay.

16:02.379 --> 16:04.122
We're losing her.

16:04.214 --> 16:05.590
- Alex?
- Yes.

16:05.674 --> 16:08.247
- You're not losing her.
- Oh, we are. She's going to high school.

16:08.343 --> 16:10.217
This is just when I lost Haley.

16:10.304 --> 16:12.925
This is when Haley went
from being my sweet little angel...

16:13.015 --> 16:18.720
to being a moody, texting,
snotty little princess who hates me.

16:18.812 --> 16:20.556
Haley doesn't hate you.

16:20.647 --> 16:22.355
And we're not losing her.

16:22.441 --> 16:24.599
Do you remember when
you used to come home from work...

16:24.693 --> 16:27.528
and Haley would meet you at the door
in her little <i>Aladdin</i> pajamas?

16:27.613 --> 16:29.985
You know, and she'd stick
her arms up in the air and say...

16:30.073 --> 16:32.695
"Daddy, Daddy, take me
on a magic carpet ride."

16:32.784 --> 16:34.409
Remember that?

16:34.494 --> 16:37.579
When was the last time
Haley was that excited to see you?

16:39.333 --> 16:42.287
- I don't remember. It's been so long.

16:42.377 --> 16:44.619
We're losing another one.

16:44.713 --> 16:47.797
That's what kids do. They leave.
They leave and they...

16:47.883 --> 16:49.840
and they don't come back.

16:49.927 --> 16:53.130
- Oh, well, ours will come back. Right?
- What if they don't...

16:53.222 --> 16:56.222
and pretty soon it's just the two of us?

16:57.434 --> 16:59.806
- I don't wanna go to Vegas anymore.
- I know.

16:59.895 --> 17:02.730
I just wanna hug 'em and embarrass 'em
in front of their friends.

17:02.814 --> 17:04.473
I know.

17:04.566 --> 17:06.440
And Alex... My God.

17:06.527 --> 17:08.186
If we miss this speech...

17:08.278 --> 17:12.857
Honey, she's a middle child.
She will never forgive us.

17:13.784 --> 17:15.492
I'm not missing that speech!

17:15.577 --> 17:17.784
- Hello! Hello!
- What's the plan, Phil?

17:17.871 --> 17:20.160
<i>Mi nombre es Felipe.</i>

17:20.249 --> 17:22.574
<i>Yo voy a la escuela.</i>

17:22.667 --> 17:24.493
- You need a ride to the school?
- Yes, please.

17:24.586 --> 17:26.079
"Felipe"?

17:31.385 --> 17:34.090
 Okay.
- <i>¡ Vámonos, muchachos!</i>

17:34.179 --> 17:37.429
<i>##  </i>

17:39.017 --> 17:41.769
I am so proud to be standing in front...

17:41.854 --> 17:43.727
of this extraordinary
group of youngsters...

17:43.814 --> 17:47.147
I'm sorry. Or should I say "oldsters"?

17:47.234 --> 17:49.725
But seriously, the word
"commencement"...

17:49.820 --> 17:51.528
means "beginning."

17:51.613 --> 17:54.104
- I'm sorry I laughed.
- I don't need an apology...

17:54.199 --> 17:57.153
but I will say your behavior today
has been very eye-opening.

17:57.244 --> 17:58.952
- No offense, Jay.
- None taken.

17:59.037 --> 18:01.279
You look like an iceberg.

18:02.958 --> 18:06.541
Okay. Senor, this is it, right here. Yeah.

18:09.965 --> 18:11.792
- Okay.
- <i>Muchas gracias, muchachos.</i>

18:11.884 --> 18:13.793
You're quite welcome.

18:15.137 --> 18:19.431
And now please welcome
your valedictorian, Alex Dunphy.

18:25.480 --> 18:27.307
 Where's my mom and dad?
- Thank you.

18:27.399 --> 18:29.392
Hmm... There they are.

18:33.405 --> 18:34.983
Principal Kaizler...

18:35.073 --> 18:36.817
- faculty...
- Phil!

18:36.909 --> 18:38.818
- School board administrators...

18:38.911 --> 18:40.239
fellow graduates...

18:40.329 --> 18:42.286
- I got you.
- Parents...

18:42.372 --> 18:44.412
- everyone who helped us through this challenging...

18:44.499 --> 18:46.741
Cam, you have lost all credibility.

18:46.835 --> 18:48.495
- It's completely different.
- How?

18:48.587 --> 18:50.414
  It's the juxtaposition
of absurdist comedy...

18:50.506 --> 18:52.831
against the backdrop of a formal setting.

18:52.925 --> 18:54.668
Not a big-boned man falling into a pool.

18:54.760 --> 18:57.167
- Really?
- Shh! This is about Alex.

18:57.262 --> 19:01.675
It's ironic that I stand up here
representing my classmates...

19:01.767 --> 19:03.261
when...

19:06.146 --> 19:08.898
they're so awesome.

19:08.982 --> 19:12.019
They should be up here themselves.

19:12.110 --> 19:13.605
But I'm up here...

19:13.695 --> 19:18.192
and... I'm sayin'... stuff...

19:18.283 --> 19:21.533
'cause... everybody's got their...

19:21.620 --> 19:23.577
stuff...

19:23.664 --> 19:25.573
whether you're popular...

19:25.666 --> 19:27.623
or a drama geek...

19:27.709 --> 19:29.204
- Oh.
- Or a cheerleader...

19:29.294 --> 19:31.038
or...

19:31.129 --> 19:32.588
even a nerd like me.

19:32.673 --> 19:35.627
- We all have our insecurities.

19:35.717 --> 19:36.915
- Yes, we do.
- Shh.

19:37.010 --> 19:38.718
We're all just trying
to figure out who we are.

19:40.556 --> 19:42.216
I guess what I'm trying to say is...

19:44.476 --> 19:48.141
don't stop believin'.

19:49.106 --> 19:51.431
Get this party started.

19:58.782 --> 20:00.573
 Nice!
 Nice job, Alex!

20:04.204 --> 20:05.663
Good job, Alex!

20:05.747 --> 20:07.242
Seriously?

20:11.378 --> 20:13.038
- There she is.
 There's our girl!

20:13.130 --> 20:15.122
Good job. Mmm!

20:15.215 --> 20:20.173
- Your speech moved me.
- I loved how you played with the song titles.

20:20.262 --> 20:22.420
- Fantastic.
- My idea.

20:22.514 --> 20:24.886
- You did good, kid.
- Thanks, Grandpa. Aaah!

20:24.975 --> 20:26.469
Don't ask. He'll be fine.

20:26.560 --> 20:28.054
We are so proud of you.

20:28.145 --> 20:30.221
- Come here.
- Hello!

20:30.314 --> 20:32.223
I opened the gate with my mind.

20:32.316 --> 20:34.854
- What do you say we all go get something to eat?
- Yeah!

20:34.943 --> 20:38.526
Actually, I was kind of
just invited to a party.

20:38.614 --> 20:40.108
- Ooh!
- Would it be okay if I go?

20:41.116 --> 20:42.943
- Yeah, of course.
- Yeah.

20:43.035 --> 20:45.407
- Thanks for comin', you guys.
 See ya, kid.

20:45.495 --> 20:47.535
- Bye, sweetie.
 Congratulations.

20:47.623 --> 20:49.781
- Hmm.
- I'm kinda hungry, Mom.

20:51.752 --> 20:53.246
Oh, my God. She's back.

20:53.337 --> 20:54.831
- Oh, my baby.
- What?

20:54.922 --> 20:55.870
- Oh, my God.

20:55.964 --> 20:57.340
- My little baby.
- What are you doing?

20:57.424 --> 20:58.622
Let's go. Let's go eat.

20:58.717 --> 21:01.290
- I'm not hungry anymore.
- You're not gonna regret this.

21:01.386 --> 21:03.759
- You are not gonna regret this.
- I'm not... I'm not hungry.

21:03.847 --> 21:05.507
- Sure, you are. Sure, you are.
- No, I'm not!

